Articles.Content:
KSP 1.0.5 32-bit (58 mods), Win7 64-bit, 12 GB RAM, Radeon HD 5700 series gfx card.

I don't know from where this came or if it's associated with a particular mod, but all of a sudden I'm getting errors in the output log:

Line xxx: ContractConfigurator.Parameters.VesselParameterGroup: Unable to get vessel display name for 'Kerbin Duo Orbiter' - ContractVesselTracker is null.  This is likely caused by another ScenarioModule crashing, preventing others from loading.

I've never named a vessel "Kerbin Duo Orbiter" nor do I think I can identify to which of 25-odd satellites it might refer.  GCMonitor shows only 3GBs used so I'm not running into the memory cap.

I also don't know if this could result in my reverting to the VAB from a vessel in orbit, only to have the game freeze.  The Loading planets are whizzing byand some of the mod buttons seem to work, but no picture of the KSC, just an otherwise black screen.

Any thoughts to where I might go with this?  I'll post the entire log if necessary, but I thought I would try to narrow the culprit down first since I don't know if the Contract Configurator is stock or a mod.

Contract configurator is a mod. It is a dependency of all contract packs. The referenced vessel name is most likely added by a contract pack. Which ones are you using? While we're at it, please list all of your mods.

1 hour ago, ExplorerKlatt said:

Contract configurator is a mod. It is a dependency of all contract packs. The referenced vessel name is most likely added by a contract pack. Which ones are you using? While we're at it, please list all of your mods.
